<db:para>The <db:emphasis>Hello Speak</db:emphasis> example demonstrates how <db:link xlink:href="qtexttospeech.xml">QTextToSpeech</db:link> can be used in a Qt C++ application to read out text, and to control the speech.</db:para>
<db:para>The example uses a <db:link xlink:href="qtwidgets-index.xml">widget UI</db:link> to provide controls for the pitch, volume, and rate of the speech. It also lets the user select an engine, the language, and a voice.</db:para>
